obo:UBERON_0002421  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_493  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: CAPS-1 mediates dense core vesicle fusion in neurons. CAPS-1 and -2 deletion reduces dense core vesicle fusion in response to electrical stimulation in neurons from hippocampal mass cultures (Fig. 3) and isolated, autaptic cultures (Fig. 4) from synapses, but also extra-synaptic sites. Live-imaging (pHluorin) experiments.\n\n12/5/2017 Pim:\n-Fig.3 shows CAPS1/2 double KO animals, but in Fig.4 it is shown that in hippocampal neurons CAPS1 is specifically involved. Therefore, no IGI of CAPS1/2 is needed.\n-based on data on SVs CAPS1 is though to mediate one of the steps of LCDV exocytosis (docking, priming, release) and therefore the \"regulates...\" box was not selected.. Experimental description: M&M: CAPS-1/2 double knockout mice..." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" ;
        dc:date           "2017-05-12" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_493" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

